episodes.title: British royals gather for Christmas service without Andrew | REUTERS
episodes.description:
King Charles led the royal family at Sandringham's Christmas church service in Norfolk, England, as Andrew Mountbatten Windsor remained absent following his removal from royal titles over ties to convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

episodes.title: DOJ says a million more potential Epstein documents were found | REUTERS
episodes.description:
The US Justice Department said that more than a million more documents potentially tied to convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein have been uncovered, delaying a full release for weeks while officials redact details to protect victims.

episodes.title: LIVE: Lawyer Gloria Allred, alleged Epstein victim Alicia Arden address media
episodes.description:
Attorney Gloria Allred and Alicia Arden, an alleged Jeffrey Epstein victim, hold a news conference in Los Angeles. It comes as U.S. President Donald Trump urges House Republicans to vote to release the Justice Department's investigative Epstein files related to the late convicted sex offender.

episodes.title: Virginia Giuffre’s brother says Andrew losing royal titles is 'true vindication' | REUTERS
episodes.description:
Sky Roberts, the brother of Virginia Giuffre, who accused Britain's ex-Prince Andrew of sexually abusing her when she was a teenager, says he felt ‘true vindication' for his sister after King Charles stripped Andrew of his title.

episodes.title: Kenya exhumes 32 bodies as outcry grows over starvation cult deaths | REUTERS
episodes.description:
The discovery of the 32 bodies in the southeastern Kenyan village of Kwa Binzaro has been linked to the same Christian sect blamed for the deaths of over 400 people in the nearby Shakahola Forest in 2023.
